The paper deals with clustering polygonal curves under the Fr\'echet distance, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The development of construction methods for $\epsilon$-coresets is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and the paper specifically mentions the size and time complexity of these coresets. The objective functions used for clustering, $(k,l)$-\textsc{center} and $k$-\textsc{median}, are common in clustering and optimization (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of polynomial and exponential functions, which are common in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on clustering and data reduction could also place it in the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
